# GitHub-native protection that complements .github/workflows/validate-release-pr.yml.
#
# Strategy:
#   - List ONLY paths that a release / dependency bot must NOT touch silently.
#   - Paths NOT listed here have no code owner -> no mandatory review under
#     "Require review from Code Owners". This is intentional: it lets the
#     `changesets-release/main` PR (which only touches CHANGELOG.md,
#     package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, and .changeset/*.md) merge without an
#     extra approval round.
#   - Anything else (source code, workflows, husky hooks, build/lint configs)
#     requires an admin review BEFORE the merge button becomes available.
#
# Pre-requisite: enable "Require a pull request before merging" and
# "Require review from Code Owners" in the branch protection rule for `main`.

# Source & build pipeline
/src/                                        @JannikZed @tilman
/scripts/                                    @JannikZed @tilman
/dev/                                        @JannikZed @tilman
/tests/                                      @JannikZed @tilman
/docs/                                       @JannikZed @tilman

# CI, hooks, supply-chain critical config
/.github/                                    @JannikZed @tilman
/.husky/                                     @JannikZed @tilman
/.npmrc                                      @JannikZed @tilman

# Lint / format / type / test config
/eslint.config.js                            @JannikZed @tilman
/.prettierrc.json                            @JannikZed @tilman
/.prettierignore                             @JannikZed @tilman
/.editorconfig                               @JannikZed @tilman
/.swcrc                                      @JannikZed @tilman
/tsconfig.json                               @JannikZed @tilman
/tsconfig.build.json                         @JannikZed @tilman
/playwright.config.ts                        @JannikZed @tilman
/vitest.config.js                            @JannikZed @tilman

# CODEOWNERS itself must not be silently rewritten
/.github/CODEOWNERS                          @JannikZed @tilman
